Key Match Events: Rohit Sharma's 92 from 41 balls set up a 24-run win for India
Travis Head's 76 kept Australia in the game
David Warner was dismissed in the first over of the chase
Mitch Marsh offered hope with 37 from 28 balls
Glenn Maxwell struck 15 off his first four balls but was bowled
Travis Head was eventually caught trying to take on Jasprit Bumrah
Post-Match Reflections: Australia's hopes of being world champions in all formats are in grave danger
The result means India qualify for the semi-finals and will face England
Australia's World Cup fate is now out of their hands
Miscellaneous Highlights: Rohit Sharma's 19-ball 50 marked the fastest ever against Australia
Josh Hazlewood slowed India down with a 1-14 performance
Glenn Maxwell switch-hit spinner Ravindra Jadeja
